message: NA

Today, I introduced bipartisan legislation to impose Congressional term limits.   Members of Congress in the House and Senate need to be focused on doing the right thing, not on doing what is best for their political careers. Term limits legislation should be a major piece of President-elect Trump's efforts to drain the swamp in Washington DC.
With the start of the 115th Congress, it's time for Republicans to deliver on campaign promises made to the American people.

The UN is directly funding an effort to boycott Israeli companies.  The measure was funded immediately following the Obama administration's support of a vote condemning Israeli settlements.  American taxpayer dollars should not be used to fund an organization that is committed to delegitimizing Israel.    The UN should be defunded.

Today, I voted for H.R. 26, the Regulations from the Executive in Need of Scrutiny Act or the REINS Act.  Congress has ceded too much power to the executive branch, leading to an avalanche of red tape and new rules which are strangling economic growth and punishing job creators.  The REINS Act will help rebalance the scales and give Congress a bigger voice in the regulatory process.
I have co-sponsored H.R. 24, The Federal Reserve Transparency Act. The American people deserve more transparency from their government.
75% percent of Americans support term limits for members of Congress. Term limits will force politicians to focus on the challenges confronting our nation rather than their re-election.
NA

American military power has not only kept our country safe and free, but also underwritten global prosperity and human freedom. Yet due to the devastating impact of sequestration, we now have the smallest Navy since before World War I.  It's time to make the US Military great again, and I'm glad to see we will soon have a Commander in Chief who is committed to doing so.

Today the U.S. House unanimously approved H.R. 353, the Lucas-Bridenstine Weather Research and Forecasting Innovation Act.  Our aim is to have zero deaths from tornadoes and other extreme weather events. This bill gets us closer to that day.
Obamacare is a failure.  Nothing but #FullRepeal.
I joined with over 100 members of Congress today to show my support for President-elect Trump's plan to move the U.S. embassy in Israel to Jerusalem.  I stand with Israel.

75% percent of Americans support term limits for Congress. Members of Congress in the House and Senate need to be focused on doing the right thing, not on doing what is best for their political careers.
There is no better choice to lead our military than General Mattis.  I'm honored to support his nomination for Secretary of Defense.

Today, I voted for the first step in repealing Obamacare.  The bill starts the so-called “reconciliation” process for repealing the failed law.  The Senate passed the same bill early Thursday.  It’s time for Republicans to deliver on their promises to fully repeal Obamacare.
Cities in this country should not be rewarded for openly defying federal immigration laws designed to protect the lives of American citizens.
NA

Over 70 countries met this weekend in Paris for a "peace" conference that excluded Israel and the Palestinians.   "Peace will not be achieved by force or from above, not at futile conferences, and not by foreign diktats. It can only be achieved in direct negotiations between the sides.” - Benjamin Netanyahu
Obamacare has been a disaster for our economy.  In addition to 300,000 jobs lost, 10,000 small businesses have shut down due to the health care law.  It's time for full repeal.

Dr. Price is a man of integrity and compassion.  He is the right man to lead the Department of Health and Human Services as we fight to repeal Obamacare and provide Americans with patient-centered health care solutions.
"Overall, the blueprint being used by Trump’s team would reduce federal spending by $10.5 trillion over 10 years."
I look forward to working with President Donald Trump to Make America Great Again! Please join me in praying for President Trump as he becomes the leader of the greatest nation on Earth.
NA

Under the Obama administration, unelected bureaucrats created an expansive, intrusive regulatory environment in an attempt to fundamentally remake the American economy.  It is encouraging  to see President Trump moving quickly to reverse many of these damaging regulations.

President Trump signed executive orders today to advance construction of the Keystone XL and Dakota Access pipelines.  This decision will result in thousands of jobs and will contribute to building a brighter energy future for America.

Today I voted to permanently ban the use of federal funds to pay for abortions. As a nation that values every individual’s right to life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness, we should always choose on the side of life.
President Trump signed an executive order today directing federal agencies to begin construction of a wall on the border with Mexico.

President Trump issued an executive order today that would strip federal money from sanctuary cities that do not enforce existing federal immigration laws. President Trump's executive actions are a solid first step in restoring the rule of law.
President Obama signed an executive order last year to prohibit certain Social Security recipients from legally owning firearms.    I will vote to reverse this assault on the 2nd Amendment next week.

My office had the honor today of presenting Corporal John "Bob" Balch with medals that he earned while serving in World War II. Corporal Balch served in the 14th Armored Division in France, Germany and Belgium.  He earned the Bronze Star for his heroic rescue of an injured fellow soldier in combat. Bob is 93 years old.  It is the dedication of soldiers like Bob, to our Constitution and our way of life, that has made the United States of America the greatest nation on earth.
NA

An amazing local organization, The Autism Center of Tulsa, has partnered with the NFL to raise awareness about those who have autism and the steps to take to create autism friendly environments. I'm proud of the work these Oklahomans are doing to help communities across the nation.
I'm glad to see President Trump is following through on his commitment to ensure our troops have the tools they need to defend freedom.

My colleague, Congressman Tom Cole, makes several excellent points in the attached statement on the President’s Executive Order on Immigration issued last Friday.  I agree that the threat to our security is very real, but the rhetoric thrown about by the critics is false and inflammatory.  Please take time to read this statement.

Chief Special Warfare Operator William “Ryan” Owens gave his life for his country last Saturday in Yemen.  My prayers are with his family during this difficult time.  “Ryan gave his full measure for our nation, and in performing his duty, he upheld the noblest standard of military service. The United States would not long exist were it not for the selfless commitment of such warriors.” -  Secretary of Defense James Mattis
NA

"Neil Gorsuch won't just restore the conservative tilt that the Supreme Court had before Antonin Scalia's death a year ago. He could help it endure for decades to come."  President Trump’s Supreme Court nominee, Neil Gorsuch, is extremely well qualified and was unanimously approved by the Senate for his current judicial appointment.  The Senate should move expeditiously with his confirmation and Democrats should stop playing obstructionist games with the President’s nominees.
Homeland Security Sec. John Kelly said this week that he would like to see the southern border wall completed in two years.  I'm glad to see progress is finally being made in securing our borders.
Today, I was proud to vote to overturn a regulation issued by the Obama administration that prohibited certain Social Security recipients from legally owning firearms.
Iran's latest missile test was a violation of UN Security Council resolutions.  I'm encouraged to see the Trump administration is serious about holding Iran accountable.

Last week, President Trump signed an order that would strip federal money from sanctuary cities that do not enforce existing federal immigration laws. Sanctuary cities receive over $27 billion from the federal government each year.

President Trump's Executive Order on immigration is simply a pause, similar to ones issued by previous presidents including Mr. Obama. It is legal and will help to balance security with access.

Judge Gorsuch's record clearly shows that he believes that judges should base their decisions on the law and the Constitution, not their own personal politics.  Gorsuch is unquestionably qualified and should be confirmed.

Americans waste almost 9 billion hours each year working on their taxes. This is ridiculous.   It's time for real tax reform, and we can begin by repealing the 16th Amendment and eliminating the IRS.   I'm proud to be a co-sponsor of H.R. 25, the FairTax Act, which does just that.
The solution Democrats are offering for fixing Obamacare is MORE government. More government is never the answer for fixing what government intervention has broken. #FullRepeal

Real tax reform will strengthen economic growth and benefit all Americans. Now is the time.
The House is planning a vote to repeal an Obama order that forced states to fund Planned Parenthood. Planned Parenthood should not get one penny from taxpayers.

Americans spend almost 9 billion hours each year working on their taxes.  Additionally, tax compliance cost the U.S. economy $409 billion in 2016.  Our tax code is far too complex. Real tax reform should simplify the process and allow Americans to fill out their taxes on a form so straightforward it will fit on a postcard.
I'm glad to see President Trump is demonstrating America's unwavering support for Israel.

Today, my staff was privileged to visit the Ernest Childers VA Outpatient Clinic in Tulsa in honor of the National Salute to Veteran Patients.    As a combat veteran, I believe it is critical we take time to stop and thank those who have sacrificed so much on our behalf.

Today, I voted to block an Obama administration regulation which opened a backdoor to funding abortion with taxpayer dollars.   This particular "Midnight Rule" was designed to support the abortion industry.  If enacted, this rule would have prohibited states from denying Federal grants to abortion providers.  Taxpayers should not be forced to fund abortions.
The IRS has been used as a weapon to unfairly target Americans based on their political beliefs.  It's time to abolish the IRS.

On February 11th, North Korea launched an extended range ballistic missile. This was followed by another emergency UN Security Council meeting which will likely result in another round of diplomatic "tough" talk coupled with ineffective sanctions.   The most effective defensive posture we can take is to ensure that North Korea knows that any future missile launches will be destroyed before reaching their targets.

President Trump is set to reverse Obama’s aggressive attempts to fundamentally transform America. Parents and schools must assert their right to govern themselves and not submit to federal bullying. I fully support the President's actions.
"I am here to underscore the ironclad support of the United States for Israel. I’m here to emphasize the United States is determined to stand up to the UN’s anti-Israel bias."

According to a Harvard–Harris Poll provided to The Hill, 80 percent of voters oppose sanctuary cities.

President Trump will sign an executive order today scrapping a controversial Obama administration rule that amounted to a land grab by the EPA. The rule was known as "Waters of the United States" or WOTUS.  Under the rule, self-contained ponds, wetlands, and ditches would be considered “navigable waters,” and thus subject to EPA regulation. The rule worked against the interests of farmers, energy producers, and landowners across this country.

It was great to be in Bartlesville last Friday. I had the opportunity to give an update at the Arvest Friday Forum and highlight the excellent work being done with the USS Oklahoma exhibit at the Bartlesville Area History Museum.
I am proud to see that the Senate will vote to confirm Neil Gorsuch to the Supreme Court this week.   His confirmation will be a victory for the rule of law.

"This means that taxpayer dollars will not be supporting organizations that promote or participate in the management of a coercive abortion program — like China’s two-child policy that includes forced abortions."

I recently voted for the Cruz-Brady bill that allows states to create drug testing requirements that must be met before citizens can receive federal unemployment benefits.  President Trump signed the bill into law.

"Army Chief of Staff Gen. Mark Milley warned that Congress's inability to pass a budget by the end of the month would 'ultimately result in dead Americans on a future battlefield' and pose a threat to national security."  I agree with Army Chief of Staff Gen. Milley, for the sake of our military and national security, Congress must return to funding the government through regular order.
Judge Neil Gorsuch has been confirmed to the Supreme Court.  Judge Gorsuch is a principled constitutionalist that is well qualified to fill the seat of Justice Scalia.

The Securing America Town Hall is tonight at 6:30 PM at the Mabee Center.  I hope to see you there!
It's shameful that the United Nations failed to condemn Syria for using chemical weapons on its own citizens.
Remember on this Good Friday the ultimate sacrifice that was made on our behalf.

It's time for real tax reform. That is why I'm a cosponsor of the FairTax Act which repeals the income tax and abolishes the IRS.

I recently cosponsored the Stop Dangerous Sanctuary Cities Act.  If passed, the bill will withhold key federal funding from both sanctuary cities and cities that simply refuse to enforce federal immigration laws.
Our tax code is overly burdensome and the agency charged with enforcement, the IRS, cannot be trusted. This is why I continue to support the FairTax, which calls for the abolishment of the IRS.

Please join me in remembrance of the tragic bombing of the Alfred P. Murrah Federal Building on April 19, 1995.  All of us remember exactly where we were that day, and we will never forget the 168 people who were killed. Terrorism is evil, yet the incredible response to tragedies like we experienced so many years ago serve to highlight the strength, resolve, and resilience of the American people to the world.

Last evening, President Trump signed into law H.R. 353, the Lucas-Bridenstine Weather Research and Forecasting Innovation Act.   This legislation prioritizes improving weather forecasts and opens opportunities for new and innovative sources of weather information.  I congratulate President Trump for moving us closer to a day when we have zero deaths from tornadoes and severe weather events.

Yesterday, President Trump signed the Veterans Choice Improvement Act, a bill that extends and expands access to private doctors for veterans that want to bypass the VA system.  This bill is the first step in President Trump's promised reforms to the VA. Our veterans fought to defend our country, and now we must deliver on our promise to provide the best possible care to our nation's heroes.

"Through the strong leadership of President Trump and Homeland Security Secretary Kelly, we have already made incredible progress and have seen the lowest number of border crossings in at least 17 years."  President Trump's decision to enforce our immigration laws is having an effect on illegal border crossings.  Now, Congress needs to work with the President to complete the border wall.

More details have come to light today on Obama's terrible Iran Nuclear Deal.  President Trump has ordered his National Security Council to review President Obama's terrible Iran Nuclear Deal.  Iran is a state sponsor of terrorism that continues to build up its ballistic missiles arsenal.

I'm a co-sponsor of the National Right-to-Carry Reciprocity Act, a bill that allows any person with a state issued concealed carry permit to carry their firearm in another state that allows concealed carry.  I believe that with the Trump administration we can finally get this bill passed and signed into law.

A new video was released yesterday of Planned Parenthood executives negotiating the sale of human baby organs. The video is the same person that joked she wanted a "Lamborghini" when prospective buyers offered to outbid other organ procurers.   Planned Parenthood receives $500 million from taxpayers each year and performs 300,000 abortions annually. Planned Parenthood must be defunded.

I attended a ceremony today with President Trump where he issued an executive order establishing a new whistleblower protection office at the VA.  This order will promote accountability at the VA by improving the process to identify and remove VA employees that fail to properly care for our veterans.

President Trump signed an order today that opened up offshore areas to job-creating energy exploration.  "Renewed offshore energy production will reduce the cost of energy, create countless new jobs and make America more secure and far more energy independent." - President Trump
I am a cosponsor of the One Subject at a Time Act, a bill that will require each piece of legislation in Congress to be limited to only one subject.

"In 1986, the San Diego Border Patrol sector accounted for approximately one-third of all apprehensions along the U.S.-Mexico border. Today, it accounts for only a small fraction."  The bottom line is that a properly built border wall works.  I support President Trump's plan to build a border wall and enhance our border security.

Americans are fed up with lengthy bills passed by Congress before members even know what they contain.   I have introduced a bill to hit the brakes on runaway legislation: the Read the Bill Act. At a minimum, our constituents expect Members of Congress to read and understand legislation before taking a vote.

"In the closing months of the Obama administration, federal agencies enacted a slew of red tape before the new cabinet secretaries arrived. The GOP Congress and Trump are now going through those rules and weeding out ones they find unacceptable."  Under the Obama Administration, unelected bureaucrats used expansive and intrusive new regulations to fundamentally remake the American economy.  President Trump so far has signed 13 pieces of legislation repealing Obama-era regulations.

Scott Garrett is an excellent choice to head the Export Import Bank. He has studied the Bank's operations and understands its intended purpose.  Scott is a reformer.  In this position he will make the reforms necessary to build confidence among Members of Congress and preserve the ExIm Bank for its intended purpose.
I support term limits. Members of Congress in the House and Senate need to be focused on doing the right thing, not on preserving their careers by getting re-elected.

President Trump is expanding President Reagan's Mexico City policy that bans U.S. funding for abortions overseas. Taxpayer dollars should never be used to fund abortions.
Exporting larger amounts of LNG will promote American energy freedom and boost our economy. This deal alone will generate $26 billion annually for the United States.

Pastor Andrew Brunson, a U.S. citizen, has been imprisoned in Turkey since October of 2016.  Dr. Brunson is being held without formal charges.  During Turkish President Erdogan's visit to the White House this week, President Trump pressured Erdogan to release Brunson from prison.  It is encouraging to see President Trump and Vice President Pence stand up for religious liberty at home and abroad.  Turkey should immediately release Dr. Brunson and return him to the United States.

Serving in the United States Military has been one of the greatest honors of my lifetime.   Today, as we recognize Armed Forces Day in the U.S., I want to thank each service member, past and present for their commitment to the security of of our nation.
After the last eight years, it's encouraging to have a commander-in-chief that is clear about his support for Israel.

I'm an original co-sponsor of Congressman Thomas Massie's bill to eliminate income taxes on Social Security benefits. The government taxes, redistributes, then taxes the redistribution.  It's time to end this practice that hurts seniors.
President Trump's first budget shows respect for the American taxpayer by reducing government bureaucracy, reining in spending, and putting us on a path to balance.

According to HHS, premiums in Oklahoma have tripled under Obamacare and our state is down to one insurance provider on the exchange.  Under the Republican plan, Americans will have more choices at lower costs.
According to the Department of Labor, jobless claims are at the lowest level in 44 years. Broader underemployment, including those forced into part-time jobs, also fell in April.

Small business owners cannot create money out of thin air to support a $15 minimum wage. Their increased costs will result in higher prices for consumers and fewer jobs. This will negatively impact the working poor the most, which is the very group of people proponents of raising the minimum wage claim they want to help.
Memorial Day Observance Ceremony

I had the honor of speaking today at the Avenue of Flags Memorial Day Weekend Observance at Floral Haven in remembrance of so many brave soldiers that paid the ultimate sacrifice for our freedom.  At this year's event, I was able to formally recognize Sgt. Ronnie Haney, a Vietnam veteran that was wounded in combat, who only recently received his full compliment of medals.

I support restoring the filibuster to its original form that required Senators to hold the floor in order to extend debate. Now, Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer can simply send an email, kill a bill, and go enjoy a steak dinner with his lobbyists.  If Democrats want to shut down the government over tax reform, the border wall, or healthcare, they should be forced to win the votes to do so.

Today I voted for the Financial CHOICE Act, a bill that reins in Dodd-Frank and delivers regulatory relief for small banks and credit unions.  This legislation will help small businesses create more jobs and give consumers more choice and access to credit.

I am a cosponsor of the Concealed Carry Reciprocity Act of 2017, a bill that allows any person with a state-issued concealed carry permit to carry their firearm in another state that allows concealed carry.  I believe this bill moves the fight to protect our 2nd Amendment right forward.

Recently I cosponsored the Expanding Veterans' Access to Choice Act. In 2014, a bill was signed into law that allowed veterans that lived more than 40 miles away from a VA medical facility to seek medical care from a private physician. However, some veterans that lived within 40 miles of the VA, but still couldn't recieve timely appoints, were not allowed to seek treatement outside the VA.  This bill establishes that veterans who live within 40 miles of a VA location but cannot access care through that location are still eligible to receive care through a private healthcare physician.
NA

The Trump administration took formal action today towards repealing the controversial Obama administration rule that amounted to a land grab by the EPA. The rule was known as "Waters of the United States" or WOTUS.  Under the rule, self-contained ponds, wetlands, and ditches would be considered “navigable waters,” and thus subject to EPA regulation. The rule worked against the interests of farmers, energy producers, and landowners across this country.

Christopher Stevens, and Sean Smith in recognition of their contributions to our nation while serving in Benghazi.  It is important that we honor these four heroes that sacrificed their lives for our country.

Today marks the 227th Birthday of the United States Coast Guard, founded in 1790 by Alexander Hamilton. We express gratitude to the Coast Guardsmen and women stationed around the world who go under appreciated every day. These men and women protect our borders daily from illicit activity by transnational criminal organizations like the Sinaloa Cartel, protect the marine environment, ensure a safe and efficient marine transportation system, create passage ways by breaking ice in the Arctic and Antarctic regions, conduct national defense missions around the world, and rescue countless lives in danger at sea. We will always stand by the Coast Guard in remaining "Semper Paratus--Always Ready" as it meets the nation's 21st century demands.
